      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "ROULLOTTIE (10) hails from the in-form Michael Travers stable, and she won third up from that yard in a weak race in her penultimate start, before a battling run for sixth as the favourite last time out at Gundagai. She drops 2kg, and if she can find an uncontested lead, then she is worth another chance. ROONAMI (6) won her maiden at Goulburn by a short head, and then was beaten by a wide gate at the Sapphire Coast last start 5 weeks ago. She can bounce back into form here. JENNI DIVINE (8) failed to fire on a heavy track at Wagga 3 weeks ago when following on from a third-place finish at Dubbo. A firmer surface would suit her, and she can make amends in a modest field. KELILAH (2) will find this easier than her last start, and on her best day, she is worth including in all top 4 combos. Stick with her. LEGENDARY DIVA (3) flipped her poor form on its head when scoring an upset win at Corowa nearly 6 weeks ago. If she can find that form again, then she can repeat the dose.",
